==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''bombard''' ([[bombarded]], bombarded, [[bombarding]])

#To [[attack]] something with [[bomb]]s, [[artillery]] [[shell]]s, or other [[missile]]s. ''Syn.'' '''to [[bomb]]'''.
#{{physics}} to direct an [[intense]] [[stream]] of high-energy [[particle]]s, usually sub-atomic or made of at most a few atoms, at a [[substance]].

'''bombard with''' ([[bombarded with]], [[bombarding with]])
#(figurative) to supply large amounts of [[information]], [[questions]], etc. to a person or entity. ''The company was bombarded with enquiries.''

